                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 714.1515/46</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">Thurston</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-28T10:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1917, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s December 22, 7 p.m. Honduran Government accepts neutral zone and
                    will withdraw all troops south and east of Merendén mountains upon Guatemala
                    withdrawing hers north and east of the Motagua River, reserving right to
                    maintain very small number police. Urge Guatemala to accept at once and troops
                    to be mutually withdrawn by January 1, 1918. Also press for answer to boundary
                    arbitration treaty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
